    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "Three different positions of the same dice are shown below. Select the symbol that will be at the top if ' $ \\% $ ' is at the bottom.<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m7m7jwtc/a27e303f-1c34-4e38-b981-8cd5dbd467c3/b32a1e00-f469-11ef-bbe5-33f4ad49c5b5/file-jaoe38c1m7m7jwtd.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m7m7jwtc/a27e303f-1c34-4e38-b981-8cd5dbd467c3/b32a1e00-f469-11ef-bbe5-33f4ad49c5b5/file-jaoe38c1m7m7jwtd.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"BITSAT 2024 Logical Reasoning - Figure Formation Question 4 English\"></p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "#"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "(C)"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "@"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "$ \\$ $"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "D"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>From Dice (1) and (2) ' $ \\% $ ' and '@' is common in both the dice, so '#' is opposite of 'cc'.</p><p>Now, from Dice (2) and (3) common symbol are '@' and rotate it in clockwise direction from the common face.</p><p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m7m7sm90/e857d7d2-a7b8-4b6c-aa74-88fd41eda958/a5492640-f46a-11ef-bbe5-33f4ad49c5b5/file-jaoe38c1m7m7sm91.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m7m7sm90/e857d7d2-a7b8-4b6c-aa74-88fd41eda958/a5492640-f46a-11ef-bbe5-33f4ad49c5b5/file-jaoe38c1m7m7sm91.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"BITSAT 2024 Logical Reasoning - Figure Formation Question 4 English Explanation\"></p><p>Hence, ' $ \\$ $ ' is at the bottom when ' $ \\% $ ' at the top.</p>",
